28.799999999999997px;"><strong>The Reign of Kutler</strong></h3>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table class=3D"c4" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspaci=
ng=3D"0" role=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspa=
ce:0pt;word-break:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"r" style=3D"padding-=
bottom:32px;"><div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;In=
ter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;=
line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">By that point, of course, most MSNBC insiders h=
ad already turned
their attention toward their new leader. In truth, Kutler=E2=80=99s =E2=80=
=9Cinterim=E2=80=9D title is itself=E2=80=A6 <em>interim</em>. Presumably s=
eeing what Zucker saw, Lazarus has expressed a great deal of confidence in =
Kutler, and is almost certain to install her in the position permanently. =
=E2=80=9CShe has my backing to make whatever decisions she thinks helps us =
in coordination with the rest of you, the leadership,=E2=80=9D Lazarus told=
 MSNBC staff on Tuesday, =E2=80=9Cand I=E2=80=99m very confident that we ha=
ve a plan to follow our mission
as it has gone on to date, and we=E2=80=99ll be able to advance who we are,=
 and advance our business in our new company.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
Of course, in the grand scheme of things, Kutler=E2=80=99s appointment does=
n=E2=80=99t change anything about the long-term trajectory of MSNBC as it v=
entures beyond the borders of the Comcast/NBCUniversal empire and into the =
wilderness. Lazarus has argued that this new, well-capitalized, and mostly =
debt-free
cable company will allow MSNBC to leverage its profits and pursue growth op=
portunities, which <em>will </em>be true for a few years. But as I <a href=
=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0d=
VYk5iV3pINGRtVXNRWlJtZ01IUT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvbWlrYS1icn=
plemluc2tpLWpvZS1zY2FyYm9yb3VnaHMtZXhjZWxsZW50LWFkdmVudHVyZS8_dXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPVRoZStCZXN0KyUyNitUaGUrQnJpZ2h0ZXN0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE1JTJG=
MjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlN=
DUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYxNSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdT=
AwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkM=
TJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoxOTg2MDQwfQ/0=
99d2842d4c8108f5f7efab009a24dd8b1b8808f381ec0c64688ae2aff37393a" style=3D"t=
ext-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">noted</a> back in November, SpinCo=
=E2=80=99s <em>real</em> fate is likely to involve an eventual sale to priv=
ate equity, which would resize the declining assets, cut budgets, and manag=
e the business for cash flow.</p><p style=3D"margin:
0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">In=
 the meantime, however, Lazarus appears to be putting the network on the st=
rongest footing possible. Kutler=E2=80=99s ascension signals real programmi=
ng ambition at a time when most broadcast and cable networks are simply man=
aging decline. In the coming weeks, Kutler will hire a new head of newsgath=
ering and head of talent and, I=E2=80=99m told, pursue high-profile talent =
acquisitions.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Meanwhile, Maddow, who=E2=80=
=99s a few months into her reduced $25 million, one-night-a-week deal, has =
announced that she=E2=80=99ll return to the network five nights a week for =
the first 100 days of the new Trump administration. This reunion tour might=
 presumably be extended, depending on how much she buoys the network=E2=80=
=99s sagging ratings. In any case, while the network <em>says </em>the low-=
rated <strong>Alex Wagner </strong>will return to the 9 p.m. hour after Apr=
il
30, few inside 30 Rock believe that will happen.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Told the news of K=
utler=E2=80=99s appointment, one industry veteran said, =E2=80=9CMSNBC is i=
nteresting again.=E2=80=9D Not necessarily, but the news will certainly ass=
uage the <em>many</em> (<em>believe me</em>) MSNBC insiders who are fearful=
 about what the SpinCo move=E2=80=94and the broader decline of the industry=
, generally=E2=80=94means for their futures, and who have spent the past th=
ree months
wondering aloud whether they should leave the network. Meanwhile, Kutler ha=
s her work cut out for her. MSNBC has lost roughly <em>half</em> of its tot=
al audience since Trump=E2=80=99s reelection, and <em>two-thirds </em>of th=
e demo audience in primetime. And if any truth is self-evident in cable new=
s, it=E2=80=99s a lot easier to be a wunderkind than it is to actually be i=
n charge.</p></div>
